description.narrative: By 2021, WCAR COs and RO are equipped to deliver results-based and equity-focused programmes for most vulnerable children, and to improve their performance, with emphasis on programming and fragile countries., which contributes to Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: RO and COs implement adequate cross sectoral strategies to improve programming excellence and achieve quality and equitable results for children.

description.narrative: WCARO supported 24 COs and the RO to develop high quality programming and fostered convergence towards the Key Results for Children as the region’s strategic contribution towards the Strategic Plan 2018-2021. Key achievements involved improvements to quality of Country Programmes including integration of the KRCs and engagement in UNSDCF planning as part of UN reform, integration of RBM, risk-informed programming and climate action into programmes, informing decision-making, the conduct of an SMR Review, the development of work plans around a KRC Common Agenda and finalizing the development of the RO Management Plan 2022-2025. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/03/2022
